        <abstract>
            <p>Is not surprised that GB cannot digest Pangenesis, but it has been an immense relief to CD in tying together large classes of facts.</p>
            <p>Sends names of men writing on crossing of plants. Criticises some French observations. Praises Hildebrand and Federico Delpino.</p>
            <p>Sends pamphlets.</p>
            <p>CD is experimenting on a large scale on difference in plants raised from self-fertilised and crossed seeds.</p>
            <p>F. Hildebrand has produced a graft-hybrid which seems to lend important support to Pangenesis.</p>
        </abstract>
